data.event: On June 10, 1875, James K.P. Dobbs received a deed from the United States government to the 40 acres (160,000 m2) of land he had homesteaded.

event.title: December 7, 1875, Dobbs and his wife, Margaret, sold

data.event: On December 7, 1875, Dobbs and his wife, Margaret, sold this 40 acres (160,000 m2) to Nellie Maupin.

event.title: May 17, 1878, Nellie Maupin and James P. Maupin sold

data.event: On May 17, 1878, Nellie Maupin and James P. Maupin sold the 40 acres (160,000 m2) to Anton Fisher.
